#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:2
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Welcome to a quick aerial tour of Kennedy Space Center in Orbiter 2016!"
msgstr ""
"Bienvenue pour une visite aérienne rapide du Centre spatial Kennedy dans "
"Orbiter !"

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:3
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid ""
"Welcome to a quick aerial tour of Kennedy Space Center in Orbiter 2016!    "
"This is a recorded flight, so just sit back and enjoy the view."
msgstr ""
"Bienvenue pour une visite aérienne rapide du Centre spatial Kennedy dans "
"Orbiter !    Ceci est un enregistrement, alors installez-vous "
"confortablement et profitez de la vue."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:5
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid ""
"Accelerating down runway 33 of the Shuttle Landing Facility (SLF) in a DG "
"type spaceplane."
msgstr ""
"Accélération en piste 33 de la Shuttle Landing Facility (SLF) à bord d’un "
"avion spatial de type DG."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:8
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Rotation and takeoff."
msgstr "Rotation et décollage."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:10
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Gear up."
msgstr "Rentrée du train."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:12
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Orbiter now supports higher texture resolutions for improved realism."
msgstr ""
"Orbiter prend désormais en charge des résolutions de textures plus élevées "
"pour un réalisme amélioré."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:13
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid ""
"Orbiter now supports higher texture resolutions for improved realism.    The "
"area around KSC has been textured from aerial photographs with a resolution "
"of about 1 meter per pixel."
msgstr ""
"Orbiter prend désormais en charge des résolutions de textures plus élevées "
"pour un réalisme amélioré. La zone autour du KSC a été texturée à partir de "
"photographies aériennes avec une résolution d’environ 1 mètre par pixel."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:15
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid ""
"While the KSC terrain is flat, Orbiter's new surface elevation support has "
"been put to use for modelling vegetation."
msgstr ""
"Même si le terrain du KSC est plat, Orbiter prend en charge le relief pour "
"modéliser la végétation."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:16
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Buzzing the Vehicle Assembly Building (VAB)."
msgstr "Survol à basse altitude du Vehicle Assembly Building (VAB)."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:18
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid ""
"Orbiter 2016 also models water surfaces more realistically than previous "
"editions."
msgstr ""
"Orbiter 2016 modélise également les surfaces d’eau de manière plus réaliste "
"que précédemment."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:20
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid ""
"Pad A of Launch Complex 39 (LC-39A) is ahead, used for launches of the "
"Apollo program, and later the Space Shuttle."
msgstr ""
"Le pas de tir A du Complexe de Lancement 39A (LC-39A) est droit devant, il a "
"servi aux lancements du programme Apollo, puis plus tard pour la Navette "
"Spatiale."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:22
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "And there is LC-39B."
msgstr "Et voici le LC-39B."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:23
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid ""
"And there is LC-39B.    Looks like a Shuttle is preparing for launch at this "
"very moment."
msgstr ""
"Et voici le LC-39B.    On dirait qu’une navette se prépare au lancement à "
"cet instant même."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:26
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "It's time to return to base. Preparing for landing."
msgstr "Il est temps de retourner à la base. Préparation à l’atterrissage."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:27
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Throttle to idle ..."
msgstr "Réduction des gaz…"

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:28
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Throttle to idle ...    Gear down ..."
msgstr "Réduction des gaz…    Sortie du train d'atterrissage..."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:30
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Coming in pretty high and fast."
msgstr "On arrive assez haut et vite."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:31
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "No need to panic ..."
msgstr "Pas de panique…"

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:32
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "No need to panic just yet ..."
msgstr "Pas de panique… Pas encore..."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:35
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Smooth and easy"
msgstr "Tout en douceur et sans effort"

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:36
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Touchdown!"
msgstr "Atterrissage réussi!"

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:37
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid ""
"There you go - not exactly a regulation landing, but it is pretty hard to "
"miss the SLF runway (it's one of the longest in the world)."
msgstr ""
"Voilà – ce n’est pas très réglementaire comme atterrissage, mais difficile "
"de rater la piste du Shuttle Landing Facility (c’est l’une des plus longues "
"au monde)."

#: C:/github/openorbiter/Flights/3 Minute Tour of Kennedy Space
#: Center/system.dat:38
msgctxt "Flight"
msgid "Thanks for watching - now it's over to you, commander."
msgstr "Merci d’avoir regardé – maintenant, à vous de jouer, commandant."
